#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:33
msgid ""
"This is long. The only consolation is that it's about all the reading you "
"have to do. Some jargon first"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:39
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tSpam = Unsolicited Bulk email, that is mail that the user did\n"
"not subscribe for. People who subscribe to a mailing list agree to\n"
"receive to bulk mail. That is solicited. Spam is not. The word is from\n"
"the film \"Monty Python and the Holy Grail\", where knights used as a\n"
"weapon the repition of the word spam.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:46
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tHam = good mail\n"
"\ta 'hit' is a test that identifies spam identifying something.\n"
"\tfalse hits are tests that hit ham.\n"
"        False Positive  = Good mail wrongly marked as spam\n"
"        False Negatives  = Spam wrongly let through\n"
"\tLint = Test validity of setup\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:52
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tSet your goals. Set your spam policy. I don't want bulk mail, I\n"
"don't want any spam in my mail,and I will accept false positives.\n"
"Relying on an isp for relaying mail, I cannot reject at smtp level, so I\n"
"silently delete spam, after checking the subjects and sender. Others\n"
"will be different, and your policy will differ accordingly.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:54
msgid "In fighting spam, you have many tools. Collect your first one."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:59
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1. From this moment on, start keeping your spam. you need every bit of\n"
"it you can hold onto, for testing. Don't read it, just store it in a\n"
"mailbox somewhere. About a Meg or two is enough. Collect a few\n"
"mailboxes with 50 or so, and at least one with a hundred.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:61
msgid "http:razor.sourceforge.net/"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:67
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"2. Razor-agents. This operates by sending checksums of mail to a central\n"
"server. If they have been reported as spam, the mail is markable as\n"
"spam. If not, the checksums are discarded and you are told the mail is\n"
"OK.  It's very good, but relies on reporting. For commercial use, send\n"
"an email (explaining your linux installation) to partners@cloudmark.com\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:69
msgid "http://www.rhyolite.com/anti-spam/dcc"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:76
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"3. DCC, The Distributed Checksum Clearinghouse. This operates as above,\n"
"sending checksums, but the dcc counts how many times it has received\n"
"that checksum. That is what it reports. The dcc also keeps all\n"
"checksums, so the server database is bigger. It goes back about six\n"
"months. The DCC is an effectiive check for bulk mail. I believe\n"
"commtouch offer a commercial service.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:78
msgid "http://spamassassin.apache.org/downloads.cgi"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:84
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"4. SpamAssassin-3.1.0 is a major revision on previous versions. It\n"
"offers heuristic or rule-based vetting of email and employs blocklists,\n"
"and several novel and unusual features. Very configurable - the\n"
"workhorse, and the PITA. Unlike most Perl applications, this one is\n"
"inclined to land 'jam side down' or in a mess, and sorting is necessary.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:90
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"5. Others exist. Notably, Amavisd-new and clamav. This is a sensible\n"
"balance for a home user. You may want clamav if you are processing mail\n"
"for windoze clients. Amavisd-new is a sort of sweeper process. The\n"
"trouble is, all run on perl, and there's a limit to any box's workload.\n"
"I may include them later.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:92
msgid "Ownerships:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/anti-spam-stuff.txt:102
msgid ""
"Preferred practise is not to run anything as root, and most of the mail "
"programs will become user 'nobody' if they find themselves running with uid "
"0. Also, you do not want to make a 'super-luser' who has everything set up "
"for him, as then if any process is breached, they have access to the whole "
"box. So mail is handled by restricted users with few privileges until the "
"delivery, which is done as the user to whom mail is delivered. The ultimate "
"in this is qmail, which has a mexican wave of processes owned by users with "
"shells like /bin/true, appearing and dissappearing playing pass-the-parcel "
"while your mail goes through."
msgstr ""

